Description: Voice dictation and transcription GUI for Linux (STT)
 Turbo Whisper is a free, open source voice dictation application for Linux.
 A SuperWhisper alternative that provides real-time speech to text (STT)
 transcription using OpenAI Whisper API or self-hosted faster-whisper-server.
 Supports 99 languages. Voice typing made easy with a beautiful GUI.
 .
 Features:
  - Global hotkey to start/stop recording from anywhere
  - Animated waveform visualization (OpenAI/ElevenLabs style orb)
  - OpenAI Whisper API compatible (works with self-hosted/local servers)
  - Auto-types transcribed text into focused window
  - Multilingual support (99 languages via Whisper)
  - System tray integration with autostart support
 .
 Perfect for voice input with AI CLI tools like Claude Code, Aider, and
 terminal applications. Great for accessibility, RSI, carpal tunnel, and
 hands-free typing.
 .
 Keywords: voice dictation, speech to text, stt, whisper gui, transcription,
 voice typing, voice input, dictation software, speech recognition, accessibility,
 rsi, carpal tunnel, hands-free, open source, free, multilingual, real-time,
 superwhisper alternative, nerd-dictation alternative, local, offline
